  "texts": [
    "We explore innovative strategies for image augmentation and enhancements, along with advanced neural network designs, inspired by recent breakthroughs in computer vision.",
    "These concepts highlight key research directions aimed at improving the performance of the existing methodologies for fossil image analysis.",
    "Data augmentation is crucial for mitigating data scarcity in fossil analysis, especially for rare specimens.",
    "By leveraging advanced computational methods, researchers can create realistic augmentations, enhancing neural network performance and robustness on underrepresented classes (Ansari and Qaraqe 2023), potentially uncovering novel insights about paleobiological and evolutionary patterns that would otherwise remain obscured.",
    "To address data scarcity in fossil analysis, we discuss advanced data augmentation techniques such as Variational Autoencoders and Generative Adversarial Networks, which have shown promise in mainstream computer vision and medical imaging, amongst other disciplines."
